                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-473-off2653 t18260914-473-crimeloc2655"></join>. On the 11th of July these breeches hung about five inches within the door; I heard the cry of Stop thief! I ran to the door, missed some things, crossed over, and found the prisoners in custody, with the breeches, twenty doors off.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-473-person2420">
                  CORNELIUS 
                  BIRDSEYE
               <interp inst="t18260914-473-person2420" type="surname" value="BIRDSEYE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-473-person2420" type="given" value="CORNELIUS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-473-person2420" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . My father lives in Old-street. I saw the prisoner, Bacon, coming from Adams' shop - I and another person met him; I had seen the prisoners in company about the neighbourhood for a quarter of an hour, and watched them, but did not see the breeches taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-473-person2421">
                  ROBERT 
                  TYRRELL
               <interp inst="t18260914-473-person2421" type="surname" value="TYRRELL"></interp>
